  "prompt": "Why am I blocked from asking questions under anonymous basis on Quora?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you are unable to ask questions anonymously on Quora. Here are some possibilities:\n\n1. **Policy Changes**: Quora's policies and features can change over time. They may have updated their anonymity features or restricted anonymous questions for various reasons, such as to improve the quality of discourse or reduce misuse.\n\n2. **Account Status**: If your account has been flagged for previous violations of Quora's policies, you might be temporarily or permanently restricted from using certain features, including anonymity.\n\n3. **Community Guidelines**: Posting questions that repeatedly violate Quora\u2019s community guidelines, even anonymously, may lead to restrictions. This can include questions that are deemed inappropriate, irrelevant, or abusive.\n\n4. **Technical Issues**: There might be technical issues or bugs affecting your ability to post anonymously. Updating your app or accessing the website from a different browser might resolve this issue.\n\n5. **Regional Restrictions**: Some features might not be available in all regions due to legal restrictions or business considerations.\n\nIf you believe there has been a mistake, you can contact Quora\u2019s support team for clarification or assistance. Always ensure that your questions comply with their community guidelines to maintain access to all features.",
